"""Analysis ``${name}`` — authored via L1-E ``bootstrap_analysis``.

Lives at ``.colony/analyses/${name}.py``. L1-A's ``discover_analyses``
walks ``.colony/analyses/*.py``, calls the ``analysis_entry()`` factory
exposed by each file, validates the returned dict against
:class:`polymathera.colony.agents.configs.AnalysisSpec`, and keys the
result by the file stem (so ``${name}`` becomes the analysis key the
``SessionAgent``'s planner sees in ``available_analyses``).

Fill in the placeholder fields and re-discover. The factory must
return every key declared on ``AnalysisSpec``; ``extra='forbid'`` is
on, so unknown keys fail validation rather than silently passing.
"""

